Third exercise

intruccions:

"alter" is the command for modify or edit the columns on the a table in a data base
"add" is the command concatenated whit "alter"
example: alter table name_of_table add name_new_column int;
remember the column need a name and a type of dato (int, varchar,etc.)

if you need delete a column you write the command "drop", is necesary use a reference "column"
example: alter table name_of_table drop column name_of_column;

remember write in you code "use database"

if you need alter data type in the table you write the command "alter" need reference "modify" is the action
example: alter table name_of_table column name_of_column type_of_dato(int, varchar,etc.) (number of characters)
code:

use prueba_db;

alter table usuario add edad int;
alter table usuario drop column edad;
alter table usuario modify column email varchar(50);
